                "author": "LambdaCast",
                "description": "Oh category theory, bastion of strange and wonderful terminology, (some might say terrible and inaccessible). Love it or hate it, you're likely to run into some terms from category theory if you spend enough time in FP land. In this episode we'll tackle some of the terms that make up the 'ism family of terms, morphism, endomorphism, isomorphism, homomorphism, and catamorphism.\n\nDenotational design talk: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bmKYiUOEo2A",
