                "podcastId": 6,
                "author": "Michael Budd, Fraser Hart, Lewis Cains, Edd Mann",
                "description": "In this weeks episode we start off by discussing Edd’s recent Server build, touching upon the hardware specifications, OS/ZFS-pool choices and monitoring configuration.\nWe then move on to highlight the value in splitting up computational intensive tasks into queued jobs, defensive programming in JavaScript and handling querying ever increasing data-sets.\nFinally, we talk about keeping on-top of Software/Dependency upgrades, moving over to platforms such as AWS and Ethereum.\n\n",
